✅ Sahi baat ye hai:
super() sirf tab zaroori hota hai jab tum parent class ka constructor
 (__init__) ya koi aur method manually call karna chahti ho.
Lekin agar parent class ka koi constructor nahi hai — ya child
 class apna constructor define hi nahi kar rahi — to Python khud
  hi implicitly (chhup kar) parent class ke methods use kar leti hai.
